{"---": 3, "layout: default": 1, "title: General Advice": 2, "On this page, we list general advice that didn't fit anywhere else.": 4, "* Set up a mailing list at which the publication chairs and all": 5, "student assistants who support you in your work can be reached.": 6, "Authors will forget to send questions and requests to that address,": 7, "but you can put it in cc when you respond, so everyone on the team": 8, "can keep track of where everything stands.": 9, "* It is a really good idea to set up a mailing list that contains": 10, "*all* book chairs (including all chairs of each workshop, not just": 11, "the one who is the official contact person) and communicate": 12, "frequently.  This is because in some cases": 13, "corresponding chairs did not forward emails to other organizers,": 14, "which cause a serious problem in communication.": 15, "* Each book has its own site in the START system (make sure they do;": 16, "sometimes the tutorials etc. forget because their is no real": 17, "reviewing, but they still need to use START to produce their": 18, "proceedings). Make sure you have manager access to each, so you can": 19, "edit their metadata. You may think that it's a good idea to let each": 20, "workshop chair set up their metadata themselves, but we strongly": 21, "recommend that you invest the effort to fill them all in by yourself": 22, "early.  This will pay off later when you avoid watching each book": 23, "chair figuring out the intricacies of the metadata themselves.": 24, "* from now on, can always use A4 paper": 25}